          <h3>1-Business fundamentals</h3>
            <p>First of all decide about the type of trading you want to do. Is it day trading, positional trading or just scalping ? Also decide the mode of trading whether cash segment or Futures or Options.</p>
            <p> Having decided the first step , try to learn about that type of trading. Read books or article about day trading/ Option Trading etc. It is not necessary to get a Ph.D. degree in this, but general awareness would not hurt.</p>
            <p>I believe that if this question is asked, part of the two steps mentioned above have already been taken care. You are an active trader looking to be a better trader. The most important thing for a trader is—- AVOID THE CLUTTER.</p>


          <h3>2-Remain focused</h3>
            <p>Like Arjuna could only see the sparrow’s eye and ignore the tree and the leaves, you have to learn to focus on few stocks which you want to trade. Black out everything else.
            Arjuna was the best ever archer for his exceptional focus.</p>
            <p>For you to become the best trader, you have to strive to achieve the same.
            Ignore the jungle that is the market and trade in either NIFTY index or at the most 2–3 stocks.
            Aim is to earn profits and not to marry the stocks.</p>
           <h3>3-Be Flexible</h3>
           <p>This is most important when trades go wrong. It hurts our ego when we are wrong. Rather than accepting and moving forward we get stuck into justification mode. This attitude causes more loss.</p>
            <p>One should be flexible enough to accept the change in the market momentum and get out of the trades or even reverse the trades.</p>
             <p>It is a cliche but it is true.</p>

            <h3>4-Plan the trade and trade the plan</h3>
            <p>Random trades lead nowhere but to randomness. We are in the market with a serious purpose. To take money. Spend some time before the market opens for planning your trade. Enter the trade only if the conditions assumed while planning exist in real time.</p>
            <p>Otherwise, no trade is always a good trade. You can not lose money by not trading.</p>

            <h3>5-Never ever trade without a stop loss in place.</h3>
            <p>It is your protection against sudden moves which can blow away the capital. A sensible stop loss always protects. It hurts but it saves.</p>
            <p>Ignore this tip at your own peril.</p>

            <p><i><b>Patience is a virtue which pays big rewards.</b></i></p>

            <h3>6-Cut your losses and let the profits run.</h3>
            <p>Follow this simple tip for real big gains. Letting the profit run is already shown above. Cutting the losses quickly is a bit of pain though. We are not conditioned for that action and therefore this should be done through a stop loss order.</p>

            <h3>7-There is a life beyond trading.</h3>
            <p>Be fully focused when the markets are open. Do not brood about it all day. Give time to family and friends. Go out for an enjoyable evening. Go out on weekends.</p>
            <p>Have a life.
            There is time for trading and there is time for life.</p>

            <p><i><b>I believe that these few tips can be the stepping stones towards better trading in stock markets.</b></i></p>

